    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "IMHO this go slightly beyond the use of `%%writefile`, when you get to such degree of specificity you can use a multiline string and `.format(**locals())` wrapped in a `with io.open(...,'w'), which is basicaly what`writefile` is :\n\n``` python\nFile: IPython/core/magics/osm.py\ndef writefile(self, line, cell):\n    # docs & arg parsing\n    with io.open(filename, mode, encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        f.write(cell)\n```\n"
